Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}(minced). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Trim, peel, and thinly slice @carrots{6%ounce}(sliced on a diagonal). Drain and rinse @chickpeas{13.4%ounce}. Dice @roma tomato{1}(diced). Finely chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}(finely chopped). Quarter @lemon{1}. Roughly chop @dried apricots{1%ounce} if necessary.

== Rice ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the shallot and half the garlic. Cook, stirring, until just softened, ~{1-3%minutes}.

Stir in @basmati rice{½%cup}, ¾ cup water, one of the @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Chicken Sausage Tagine ==

While rice cooks, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} and half the @Turkish spice blend{1%tablespoon}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Remove from pan and set aside.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add carrots; cook, stirring, until softened and lightly browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add remaining shallot, remaining garlic, remaining @Turkish spice blend{1%tablespoon}, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine ⅓ cup water and remaining @chicken stock concentrate{1}.

Pour stock mixture into pan with veggies.

Stir in sausage, chickpeas, and tomato. Bring to a low simmer, then cover pan. Cook until liquid is slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a second small bowl, combine @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, a pinch of @salt{}, and as much @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} as you like. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in half the cilantro, @butter{1%tablespoon}, and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice between plates or #bowls{} and top with tagine, sauce, apricots, and remaining cilantro. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.